Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning

Cardio Good Fitness Project

Ravi Potlachervu

Objective¶

Cardio Good Fitness retail store team provided a dataset to identify differences between the customers of each product and explore the relationships between the different of the customers.

  • Perform customer profiles the products sold by Cario Good Fitness.
  • Perform univariate and multivatiate analyses.
  • Generate a set of insights and recommendations that will help the company in targeting new customers.

Dataset:¶

  • Product - The model no. of the treadmill.
  • Age - Age of the customer in no of years.
  • Gender - Gender of the customer.
  • Education - Education of the customer in no. of years.
  • Marital Status - Marital status of the customer.
  • Usage - Avg. # times the customer wants to use the treadmill every week.
  • Fitness - Self rated fitness score of the customer (5 - very fit, 1 - very unfit).
  • Income - Income of the customer.
  • Miles- Miles that a customer expects to run.

Observations

  • Product: There are 3 unique product types-['TM195' 'TM498' 'TM798'] and TM195 is top selling item with 44% and followed by 'TM498' with 33%.
  • Age: Average age of customers is 28yrs and range from 18 to 50 yrs.
  • Gender: Gender has 2 unique categorical values ['Male' 'Female'] and majority of products bought by gender type 'Male'.
  • Education: Customers education years range from 12 to 21 yrs with avg of 15yrs.
  • MaritalStatus: Marital Status has 2 unique values ['Single' 'Partnered'].
  • Usage: On average the products usage is aroung 3 miles and range between 2 to 7 miles.
  • Fitness: Average fitness level of customers is 3 and range from 1-5,
  • Income: Customers income range from 29K to 105K.
  • Miles: Average customer exptect to run is 103 miles and range from 21 to 360 miles. There is huge difference between maximum value and the 75% percentile that indicates there be outliers on this column.

Univariate Analysis¶

Lets check data distribution on numerical columns

In [173]:
#create a variable to get list of numerical columns
num_col=data.select_dtypes(include=np.number).columns.tolist()
In [109]:
#Create a function to combined histogram and boxplot  graphing
def hist_box(col):
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2,figsize=(10, 3))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x=col, kde=True, ax=axs[0]);
    sns.boxplot(data=data, x=col, ax=axs[1]);
In [110]:
#Create to both histgram and boxplot graph for all numerical columns.
for i in num_col:
    hist_box(data[i]) # Call hist_box function for each column.

Observations

Age

  • Age distribution is more right skewed.
  • Very few outliers toward right.
  • Majority of products are bought age group between 20 to 40 and very less number of before 20 and after 40.

Education

  • Majority of customers have 14 to 18 years of eduction.
  • Very few outliers towards right.

Usage

  • Usage distribution is more right skewed.
  • Most of users use products about 2 - 4 times/week.
  • There are very few outliers towards right.

Fitness

  • Fitness data shows more left skewed
  • Very few number of customers have low fitness score.
  • Very few outlier towards left.

Income

  • Income data is more skewed towards right.
  • There are wide range outliers on this column. However values seems to be valid and we are going treat these values
  • Majority of customers income range from 30K to 70K.
  • There are not many customer who earn more than 70K

Miles

  • Miles distribution is more right skewed.
  • There are many outliers toward right. Mile period unit period is provide, with common I guess these are yearly basis values. I dont see any significance to remove outliers.* If its /week value most of values will outliers.
  • Most of the customers run between 50 to 130 miles/yr with average of 80 mile/year.
  • There are not many customers who run more than 200 miles/yr

Outlier Detection and Treatment¶

  • Based on the above observation will not remove any outliers.

Creating bins for Age bins

We will use pd.cut funtion to create bins on Age column

In [188]:

data['AgeType'] = pd.cut(data['Age'],bins=[15,25,35,45,55],labels=['Young','Young Adults','Middle-Aged Adults', 'Old Adults'], right = False)

  • Usage column has more correlation with Income, Miles, Fitness and education. Indicates customer use more has high fitness scores. More miles customer runs high is fitness score.
  • Income column has high correlation with Age, education, Usage, Fitness and Miles.

Conclusion¶

  • CardioFitness sells three different Treadmill products (TM195,TM498,TM798).
  • Most selling product is TM195 and followed by TM498 and least selling is TM798. I guess TM798 is highend and expensive product.
  • There are more Male buyers than female. Recommend company focus more marketing towards male customers.
  • Couples bought more products than Singles.
  • TM195 product is more bought by Couples.
  • Customers with fitness level below 3 more likely to by TM195 and TM498.
  • Customers who used TM798 have hight fitness levels.
  • Most of the products are bought by customers with 16 yrs of education.
  • TM198 is popular among customers with 18 yrs of education
  • Customers with 20 yrs eduction only bought TM798 model.
  • Customer with higher income above 70K prefer to buy TM798. Most of the customers have income below 70K and they they prefer to buy TM195 and TM498 models
  • TM195 is more popular among 'Young'(15-25), 'Young Adults(25-35)' and Middle-Aged Adults(35-45) groups.
  • TM195 model is more popular for customers will low income levels(29K-59K).
  • TM798 is more popular among High income customers (79K - 104K).
  • I include outlier on Bivariate Analsys, as I dont see any importance to exclude outliers.

Customer Profiling¶

  • Based on above analysis, I recommend Cardio Fitness should do more marketing on TM798 and target customers with higher income and higher education years to improve sales.

  • TM195 and TM498 is more popular among young and young Adult customers, targeting younger crowd may increase sales of these models.

  • Target marketing customers with education years above 16yrs. They more like to buy fitnes products.
